Hi <@UCTAN7RPA>, good morning, I am still waiting on internal response on the challenges. In terms of the business goal are you trying to display a dynamic button based on results from hubdb query? From my testing I have the following results (if not using module fields)

```&lt;div&gt;

  &lt;br&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;
  {% set _stage = contact.lifecyclestage|default('Customer') %}
  Lifecycle Stage {{ _stage }}
  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
  Module Value Before Update: {{ module.instance1 }} &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
  {% set module.instance1 = "Good Bye" %}
  {% set module.instance1 = "Good Bye" %}
  Module Value After Update: {{ module.instance1 }} &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

  {% set _var = "Hello" %}
  Variable Value Before Update: {{ _var }} &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
  {% set _var = "Good Bye" %}
  Variable Value After Update: {{ _var }} &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

  {% if _stage == "Lead" %}
    &lt;p&gt;{{ module.instance1 }}&lt;/p&gt;
  {% elif _stage == "Customer" %}
    &lt;p&gt;{{ module.instance2 }}&lt;/p&gt;
  {% else %}
    &lt;p&gt;
    {{ module.instance3 }}
    &lt;/p&gt;
  {% endif %}
  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

  {% for row in hubdb_table_rows(6346128, "stage="~contact.lifecyclestage|default('Customer')) %}
    Stage: {{ row.stage }} &lt;br&gt;
    Result: {{ row.result }} &lt;br&gt;
    Module Value: {{ module.instance1 }} &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
    {% cta "my_cta" guid='{{ row.cta_guid }}' %}
  {% endfor %}


&lt;/div&gt;```
